Package datastructures.queues

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PriorityQueue<T>
    A PriorityQueue is an extension of a Queue.
    Queue<T>
    An interface for queues.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CircularArrayQueue<T>
    A CircularArrayQueue is an implementation of a Queue based on a one-dimensional array which can wrap around.
    HeapPriorityQueue<T>
    HeapPriorityQueue is a priority queue implemented as a heap.
    LinearArrayQueue<T>
    LinearArrayQueue is an implementation of queues based on a simple linear array.
    LinearPriorityQueue<T>
    LinearPriorityQueue is a priority queue implemented as an array of common FIFO queues, where the queues themselves hold objects with the same priority in the order they arrived.
    LinkedQueue<T>
    A LinkedQueue is a queue which uses a DoublyLinkedList as the underlying implementation.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    EmptyQueueException
